<title>USA: U.S. HEADLINE STOCKS -- Issues to watch - March 19.</title>
<headline>U.S. HEADLINE STOCKS -- Issues to watch - March 19.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Stocks to watch this morning:</p>
<p>* Several U.S. high technology stocks were lower in London trading after the Wall Street Journal said a bear market may have already descended on the techs, which could spell trouble ahead for the rest of the market.</p>
<p>Compaq Computer Corp slipped 1/2 to 74-3/8, Microsoft Corp eased 1/2 to 99-1/8, Intel Corp fell 3/8 to 136-3/8, and International Business Machines Corp fell 3/8 to 139.  </p>
<p>* American List Corp announced Wednesday that it had signed a definitive agreement to merge with Snyder Communications Inc in a stock swap. It said Snyder would issue one share for each of American List's 4.5 million shares. American List closed at 22-3/8. Snyder closed at 26-1/4.</p>
